* P873D vactrol (LED + LDR optocoupler) - static model
* Full on-scan marking (KLM-76 VCA / KLM-63 MOD-VCA sheets): HTV P873-G35-201B
*
* Phase 1: the CV-controlled element is modeled as a plain resistance R,
* the steady-state LDR resistance for a given LED drive (plan Phase 1 step 3).
* Useful range on the KLM-62: roughly 1k (bright) .. 1M (dark).
*
* Dynamics (fast attack ~ms, slow resistance-dependent decay ~10..100s of ms)
* are modeled at the DSP layer (dsp/vactrol.dsp, plan Phase 3b). If a SPICE
* transient model is needed later, replace RLDR with a behavioral resistor
* driven by an RC lag network on the LED current.
.subckt P873D p n R=47k
RLDR p n {R}
.ends
